text: Magenta is a commune in the Marne department in northeastern France. In 2019, 1,697 people lived there. It was named after the 1859 Battle of Magenta, now in Italy. == Twin town == Magenta is twinned with: * Magenta, Italy, since 2009 == Related pages == * Communes of the Marne department == References == Category:Communes in Marne
title: Magenta, Marne
